title="Abstract Algebra">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 0.2</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For any integers <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a,b\in \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>, there exists <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q,r\in \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0\leq  r<|b|]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a=qb+r]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>We could take <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\{a-qb\mid  q\in \mathbb {Z},a-qb\geq 0\}]]></fr:tex>, then apply the <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0001.xml"
addr="nt-0001"
title="Well-ordering principle">Well-ordering principle</fr:link> to give us <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> as a minimal element of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
